content.description: Starts in the crack system to the right of "keymaster." Finish same as "key master."

Taken from SoMo Google doc managed by Travis K: goo.gl/maps/KMZkwcWd1yeeV1ej7  To the right of "gatekeeper". starts low on crimps, works up and right to finish on slopers. Sit down start, match hands, on lowest ledge. Lots of variations you could do here.
content.location: Park near white tank, head south and you should be able to see the boulder from the trail. You're going to need supplemental guide to direct you to the exact boulder. Use the Google Maps repository that people have been keeping for SoMo: google.com/maps/d/embed?mid…

content.description: Taken from SoMo Google doc managed by Travis K: goo.gl/maps/KMZkwcWd1yeeV1ej7Start low on crimps. Dyno or work through more crimps to gain jug up and to the left of the start.

content.description: SDS as far left to the boulder as possible in the split. Traverse the boulder by following the crack all the way over the tree, topping out above the start of Gatekeeper where it opens up. Avoid holds above the crack as they may be insecure.
content.location: Tree jetting out from the boulder splits the problem in half.

content.description: Boulder is in the shade for the most part of the morning. Solid spot to warm up.
